{
  "text": "a number of studies reported damages to soil structure and negative effects on vegetation near roads [CITATION_1] addison 2000, CzerniawskaKusza et al. 2004) or negative impacts of deicing salt on terrestrial organisms in laboratory tests [CITATION_2] . on the other hand, relatively few studies have dealt with the impact of deicing salts on soil microbial community so far. the inhibition of sensitive soil microorganisms was observed at naCl concentration of 90 mg/l and soil nitrification was significantly reduced at the concentration of about 100 mg/kg sodium and 150 mg/kg chlorides [CITATION_3] . in this study we focused on evaluating effects of road salting on soil microorganisms in real field situation.",
  "correct_citation": {
